        <div class="content-section conclusions">
            <h2 class="section-title">Strategic Conclusions & Recommendations</h2>
            
            <h3 style="margin: 30px 0 20px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;">Business Performance Analysis</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                The furniture business demonstrates solid revenue performance with $742K in total sales, though the 2.5% profit margin 
                suggests opportunities for margin improvement through strategic pricing optimization and cost management initiatives.
            </p>
            
            <h3 style="margin: 30px 0 20px 0; font-size: 1.3rem;">Actionable Recommendations</h3>
            <ul class="recommendation-list">
                <li><strong>Consumer Segment Focus:</strong> Invest additional marketing resources in the consumer segment, which generates 53% of total revenue</li>
                <li><strong>Holiday Season Optimization:</strong> Develop comprehensive Q4 marketing campaigns to capitalize on December peak performance</li>
                <li><strong>Supply Chain Enhancement:</strong> Optimize shipping operations to reduce the 28% of orders taking 4+ days</li>
                <li><strong>Geographic Expansion:</strong> Replicate California and NYC success strategies in other major metropolitan markets</li>
                <li><strong>Product Portfolio Growth:</strong> Expand chair offerings and explore complementary furniture categories</li>
                <li><strong>Margin Improvement:</strong> Implement value-based pricing strategies and supplier negotiations to improve profitability</li>
                <li><strong>Corporate Segment Development:</strong> Develop B2B sales strategies to grow the corporate segment beyond current $229K</li>
            </ul>
            
